&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 4 Skin Cancer Tracker - WVT Employees Only&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dermatology and Plastic Surgery Department &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fixed Term/ Secondment Opportunity (Internal Advert)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a motivated and enthusiastic individual currently working within Wye Valley NHS Trust to join the skin cancer team as a Skin Cancer Tracker for 37.5 hours per week, on a 12 month fixed term basis. The required hours of the post will be Monday – Friday 08:30 – 16:30.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a busy role supporting both the Dermatology and Plastic Surgery departments. We are looking for an individual who will be highly motivated to make a difference and ensure all our skin cancer patients are monitored closely, mitigating the risk of patients being missed. As a department we strive to provide excellent care to all our patients. This role is pivotal in supporting this for our Skin Cancer patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will require excellent organisational and communication skills, demonstrate the ability to work self-sufficiently, using their own initiative and be willing to be adaptable and flexible to meet the needs of the service. The individual must also have the ability to work well under pressure and have the desire to provide a first class service for patients and the clinical teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Internal opportunity for current employees of Wye Valley NHS Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
